The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Bonus unveiled

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, June 14: M amp;M brought cheer to its shareholders by declaring a bonus of 1:1. The issue comes after the company recently declared a dividend of 100 per cent and a special dividend of 30 per cent. Both add up to Rs 13 per share. 

 The announcement revved up M amp;M shares to Rs 548.60 on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE). They had scaled an intra-day high of Rs 557.40 earlier in a session where the sensex closed with a 27-point increase at 6860.18.




